# Conventional Commits

All commit messages MUST follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/).

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>)?: <description>
```

## Required types

- `feat:` — new feature (minor bump)
- `fix:` — bug fix (patch bump)
- `chore:` — maintenance, tooling, config (e.g. release-please, workflows)
- `docs:` — documentation only
- `style:`, `refactor:`, `perf:`, `test:`, `build:`, `ci:` — use when relevant
- `feat!:` or `fix!:` — breaking change (major bump)

## Examples

- `chore: add release-please configuration and update documentation`
- `feat: add custom slash commands`
- `fix: resolve input scroll on resize`

When generating commit messages, always start with a type prefix.
